  "local_port": 44088,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best stem cell research labs in India for doing masters dissertion project on stem cell?",
  "response": "India has several renowned research institutions and laboratories that are actively involved in stem cell research, making them ideal for pursuing a master's dissertation project in this field. Below is a list of some of the best stem cell research labs in India:\n\n---\n\n### **1. National Centre for Biological Sciences (NCBS), Bangalore**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell biology, regenerative medicine, and developmental biology.\n   - **Key Features:** State-of-the-art facilities, interdisciplinary research, and collaborations with international institutions.\n   - **Website:** [www.ncbs.res.in](https://www.ncbs.res.in)\n\n---\n\n### **2. Institute for Stem Cell Science and Regenerative Medicine (inStem), Bangalore**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell biology, tissue engineering, and regenerative medicine.\n   - **Key Features:** Dedicated to stem cell research, offers cutting-edge laboratory facilities, and provides opportunities for students to work with leading scientists.\n   - **Website:** [www.instem.res.in](https://www.instem.res.in)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Centre for Cellular and Molecular Biology (CCMB), Hyderabad**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell research, gene editing, and developmental biology.\n   - **Key Features:** Internationally recognized for its research output and advanced infrastructure.\n   - **Website:** [www.ccmb.res.in](https://www.ccmb.res.in)\n\n---\n\n### **4. Indian Institute of Science (IISc), Bangalore**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell biology, molecular biology, and regenerative medicine.\n   - **Key Features:** Offers interdisciplinary research opportunities and access to world-class facilities.\n   - **Website:** [www.iisc.ac.in](https://www.iisc.ac.in)\n\n---\n\n### **5. Translational Health Science and Technology Institute (THSTI), Faridabad**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell research, immunology, and translational medicine.\n   - **Key Features:** Focuses on translating research into clinical applications.\n   - **Website:** [www.thsti.res.in](http://www.thsti.res.in)\n\n---\n\n### **6. All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS), New Delhi**\n   - **Focus:** Clinical applications of stem cells, regenerative medicine, and tissue engineering.\n   - **Key Features:** Strong emphasis on translational research and access to clinical samples.\n   - **Website:** [www.aiims.edu](https://www.aiims.edu)\n\n---\n\n### **7. National Institute of Immunology (NII), New Delhi**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell biology, immunology, and developmental biology.\n   - **Key Features:** Offers a vibrant research environment and opportunities for interdisciplinary studies.\n   - **Website:** [www.nii.res.in](https://www.nii.res.in)\n\n---\n\n### **8. Tata Institute of Fundamental Research (TIFR), Mumbai**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell biology, developmental biology, and molecular biology.\n   - **Key Features:** Known for its strong research culture and international collaborations.\n   - **Website:** [www.tifr.res.in](https://www.tifr.res.in)\n\n---\n\n### **9. Manipal Institute of Regenerative Medicine (MIRM), Manipal**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell research, regenerative medicine, and tissue engineering.\n   - **Key Features:** Clinical and translational research focus with state-of-the-art facilities.\n   - **Weightsite:** [www.manipal.edu](https://www.manipal.edu)\n\n---\n\n### **10. Rajiv Gandhi Centre for Biotechnology (RGCB), Thiruvananthapuram**\n   - **Focus:** Stem cell biology, cancer stem cells, and regenerative medicine.\n   - **Key Features:** Offers a strong research environment and collaborations with international labs.\n   - **Website:** [www.rgcb.res.in](https://www.rgcb.res.in)\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Securing a Project:**\n1. **Contact Professors:** Reach out to faculty members or principal investigators (PIs) working in stem cell biology via email with your CV and a brief research interest statement.\n2. **Check Internship Programs:** Many institutions (e.g., inStem, CCMB) offer summer/winter internships that can lead to longer-term projects.\n3. **Funding:** Explore scholarships or fellowships like DST-INSPIRE, CSIR-UGC NET, or institutional funding for master\u2019s projects.\n\nThese labs provide excellent opportunities to engage in cutting-edge stem cell research and gain valuable experience for your dissertation.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
